
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Github Desktop yek barname-ye rooye mize kar (desktop application) ast baraye kar kardan ba Github. Be shoma komak mikonad ke taghirat ra be repository-haye khod ezafe va be Github beferestid (push konid).

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 Clone kardan Repository: ⬇️  Download kardan yek repository az Github be computer-e shoma.
    🔹 Commit kardan Taghirat: ✅  Save kardan taghirat dar file-haye shoma ba yek payam.
    🔹 Push kardan Commit-ha: ⬆️  Upload kardan commit-haye shoma be Github.
    🔹 Branching: 🌿  Sakhtan yek shakh-e jadid baraye kar kardan rooye feature-haye jadid bedoon tagheer dade-haye asli.
    🔹 Pull kardan Taghirat: 📥  Download kardan taghirat az Github be computer-e shoma baraye hamahang shodan ba akharin version.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    1.  Baz kardan Github Desktop va clone kardan yek repository az Github.
    2.  Anjam dadan taghirat dar file-haye project-e shoma.
    3.  Commit kardan taghirat ba yek payam-e tozihi.
    4.  Push kardan commit-ha be Github.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    Faraayand-e estefade az Github Desktop be in shekl ast:
    1. Clone → taghir → commit → push.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    GitHub Desktop is a desktop application that allows you to interact with GitHub repositories. It simplifies the process of adding changes and pushing them to GitHub.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 Clone Repository: ⬇️ Download a repository from GitHub to your computer.
    🔹 Commit Changes: ✅ Save changes to your files with a descriptive message.
    🔹 Push Commits: ⬆️ Upload your commits to GitHub.
    🔹 Branching: 🌿 Create a new branch to work on new features without affecting the main codebase.
    🔹 Pull Changes: 📥 Download changes from GitHub to your computer to stay up-to-date.

🛠 **Examples:**

    1. Open GitHub Desktop and clone a repository from GitHub.
    2. Make changes to your project files.
    3. Commit the changes with a descriptive message.
    4. Push the commits to GitHub.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    The workflow of using GitHub Desktop typically involves:
    1. Clone → Change → Commit → Push.

